https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/l4hdXxAVlaP9Bxgk4d75xhxxOrZ.jpg December, 31st. Impossible Moscow traffic, an endless rush leading to nothing, people trying to help but not making things any better. Small talk… about small things that fill one’s life — and make it pass us by too quickly. About Dad, who’s only got a few weeks left to live — and there’s nothing you can do to help... About plans for life of a 15-year-old girl — should she become a cancer specialist or a food designer? And Here's What's Happening to Me
